Only one deity, Futsunushi-no-Mikoto, is enshrined; however, ''Meiji Shrine Register'' states "deity unknown."

The founding date is unknown. Its Meiji-era rank was {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Unranked Shrine|1=UNKNOWN}}. On December 25, Meiji 40 ({{ill|lt=1907|Q2048|qid=Q2048|1=1907}}), it was merged into {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kokubu Shrine|1=UNKNOWN}} (Kokubu Ichiba, Kashiwara) and became a precinct shrine there. In March Showa 47 ({{ill|lt=1972|Q2476|qid=Q2476|1=1972}}), shrine buildings were rebuilt at the former site. A precinct shrine (Morimoto Shrine) inside Kokubu Shrine still exists.

